Express Request Functions (req) â€“ Complete Reference
What is Express Request Object?

The Request object (req) represents the HTTP request and contains information about:

URL

Parameters

Query strings

Headers

Body data

app.get('/user', (req, res) => {
  console.log(req);
});

1. req.params
Purpose

Gets route parameters.

Example
app.get('/user/:id', (req, res) => {
  res.send(req.params.id);
});

URL
/user/101

Output
{ id: '101' }

2. req.query
Purpose

Gets query string parameters.

Example
app.get('/search', (req, res) => {
  res.send(req.query);
});

URL
/search?name=ram&age=20

Output
{ name: 'ram', age: '20' }

3. req.body
Purpose

Gets request body data (POST/PUT).

Middleware Required
app.use(express.json());
app.use(express.urlencoded({ extended: true }));

Example
app.post('/login', (req, res) => {
  console.log(req.body);
});

4. req.headers
Purpose

Returns all request headers.

Example
console.log(req.headers);

5. req.get()
Purpose

Gets a specific header value.

Example
req.get('Content-Type');

6. req.method
Purpose

Returns the HTTP method used.

console.log(req.method); // GET, POST, PUT

7. req.url
Purpose

Returns request URL.

console.log(req.url);

8. req.originalUrl
Purpose

Returns the original request URL.

console.log(req.originalUrl);

9. req.path
Purpose

Returns path of the request.

console.log(req.path);

10. req.protocol
Purpose

Returns protocol used (http or https).

req.protocol;

11. req.hostname
Purpose

Returns host name.

req.hostname;

12. req.ip
Purpose

Returns client IP address.

req.ip;

13. req.secure
Purpose

Checks if request is HTTPS.

req.secure; // true / false

14. req.cookies
Purpose

Access cookies.

Middleware Required
const cookieParser = require('cookie-parser');
app.use(cookieParser());

req.cookies;

15. req.signedCookies
Purpose

Access signed cookies.

req.signedCookies;

16. req.accepts()
Purpose

Checks acceptable response types.

req.accepts('json');

17. req.is()
Purpose

Checks request content type.

req.is('application/json');

18. req.xhr
Purpose

Checks if request is AJAX.

req.xhr; // true / false

19. req.route
Purpose

Returns current route info.

req.route;

20. req.baseUrl
Purpose

Returns matched router path.

req.baseUrl;

21. req.subdomains
Purpose

Returns subdomains.

req.subdomains;

Summary Table (Viva Friendly)
Function	Use
req.params	Route parameters
req.query	Query strings
req.body	Request body
req.headers	Request headers
req.get()	Single header
req.method	HTTP method
req.url	URL
req.ip	Client IP
req.cookies	Cookies
req.accepts()	Accepted types
